<p>No, creating multiple accounts with whatever level of investment of effort is sufficient to avoid detection is the way to go. And also too easy to be worth bothering with for a reward of no external value. There are systems to game that pay off in dollars.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_17je"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_17je" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_17je')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_17je" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_17je')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_17je" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1co/rationality_quotes_october_2009/17je?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_17je" href="#17j8" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_17je" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_17je')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_17je class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_17je" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_17je" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_17je" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_17mj" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_17mj" class="parent"><a name="17mj" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_17mj" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_17mj" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_17mj" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/gwern/">gwern</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">27 October 2009 10:56:47PM</span><span class="votes " >0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_17mj'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_17mj')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_17mj" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_17mj" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/gwern/">gwern</a></span></