ints', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1786')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1786" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Upvoted because it echoes my attitude towards your and Eliezer's ideas on decision theory, except I don't keep quiet.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1786"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1786" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1786')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1786" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1786')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1786" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1co/rationality_quotes_october_2009/1786?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1786" href="#1782" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1786" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1786')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1786 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1786" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_17am" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_17am" class="parent"><a name="17am" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_17am" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_17am" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_17am" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/hegemonicon/">hegemonicon</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">23 October 2009 10:30:34PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_17am'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_17am')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_17am" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_17am" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/hegemonicon/">hegemonicon</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">23 October 2009 10:30:34PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_17am'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_17am'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_17am')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_17am" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>the human mind is trained by the knowledge imparted to it and the direction given to its ideas. Only what is great can make it great; the little can only make it little.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>-Carl von Clausewitz</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_17am"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_17am" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_17am')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_17am" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_17am')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_17am" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1co/rationality_quotes_october_2009/17am?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_17am" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_17am')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_17am class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_17am" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_178t" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_178t" class="parent"><a name="178t" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_178t" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_178t" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_178t" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Daniel_Burfoot/">Daniel_Burfoot</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">23 October 2009 02:18:17PM</span><span class="votes " >2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_178t'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_178t')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_178t" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_178t" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Daniel_Burfoot/">Daniel_Burfoot</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">23 October 2009 02:18:17PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_178t'>2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_178t'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_178t')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_178t" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>The carting of manure had to begin earlier, so that everything would be finished before the early mowing. The far field had to be ploughed continually, so as to keep it fallow. The hay was to be got in, not on half shares with the peasants, but by hired workers.</p>
  
  <p>The steward listened attentively and obviously made an effort to approve of the master's suggestions; but all the same he had that hopeless and glum look, so familiar to Levin and always so irritating to him. This look said: "That's all very well, but it's as God grants."</p>
  
  <p>Nothing so upset Levin as this tone. But it was a tone common to all stewards, as many of them as he had employed. They all had the same attitude toward his proposals, and therefore he now no longer got angry, but became upset and felt himself still more roused to fight this somehow elemental force for which he could find no other name than "as God grants", and which was continually opposed to him.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>-- Leo Tolstoy, "Anna Karenina"</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_178t"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_178t" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_178t')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_178t" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_178t')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_178t" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1co/rationality_quotes_october_2009/178t?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_178t" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_178t')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_178t class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_178t" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_178t" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_178t" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_17ce" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_17ce" class="parent"><a name="17ce" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_17ce" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_17ce" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_17ce" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/billswift/">billswift</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">24 October 2009 04:02:37PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_17ce'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_17ce')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_17ce" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_17ce" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/billswift/">billswift</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">24 October 2009 04:02:37PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_17ce'>0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_17ce'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_17ce')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_17ce" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>I think fatalism may be a key moral failing from which many others, such as carelessness and an indifference to the suffering of others, spring.  Fatalism is more common, I think, than many others seem to believe.  It does not need to be gloomy as the Slavic versions, think of the words to <em>Que Sera, Sera</em>;  <em>"whatever will be, will be"</em>.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_17ce"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_17ce" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_17ce')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_17ce" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_17ce')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_17ce" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1co/rationality_quotes_october_2009/17ce?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_17ce" href="#178t" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_17ce" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_17ce')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_17ce class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_17ce" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_177n" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_177n" class="parent"><a name="177n" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_177n" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_177n" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_177n" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/epistememe/">epistememe</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">23 October 2009 06:03:28AM</span><span class="votes " >6 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_177n'] = ['5 points', '6 points', '7 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_177n')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_177n" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_177n" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/epistememe/">epistememe</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">23 October 2009 06:03:28AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_177n'>6 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_177n'] = ['5 points', '6 points', '7 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_177n')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_177n" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>There are two mistakes one can make along the road to truth…not going all the way, and not starting.</p>

<p>Buddha</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_177n"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_177n" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_177n')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_177n" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_177n')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_177n" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1co/rationality_quotes_october_2009/177n?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_177n" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_177n')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_177n class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_177n" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_177n" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_177n" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_179r" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_179r" class="parent"><a name="179r" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_179r" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_179r" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_179r" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/wedrifid/">wedrifid</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">23 October 2009 05:55:18PM</span><span class="votes " >5 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_179r'] = ['4 points', '5 points', '6 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_179r')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_179r" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_179r" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/wedrifid/">wedrifid</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">23 October 2009 05:55:18PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_179r'>5 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_179r'] = ['4 points', '5 points', '6 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_179r')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_179r" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Well, at least Buddha started. If he'd gone a bit further along that particular road he may have added:</p>

<ul>
<li>Going the wrong way.</li>
<li>Making sacrifices to further a journey along the road to truth that do not give commensurate reward.</li>
<li>Trying to go further or faster than you are able and damaging your existing progress in the process.</li>
<li>Building (and continuing to build) your model of truth on inefficient foundations.</li>
<li>Spending resources (time, money, attention) on truth seeking now when such resources could have been used to generate far more resources for truth production later on.</li>
<li>Learning low value truth before higher relevance truth.</li>
<li>Assuming that it is possible to go all the way on the road to truth. Apart from the potential for ever more precision, every moment that passes allows matter to slip out of the reach of your future light cone. So if you manage to grab all the truth in one direction you're probably never going to get the chance to build an accurate model of the other extreme.</li>
</ul></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_179r"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_179r" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_179r')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_179r" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_179r')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_179r" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1co/rationality_quotes_october_2009/179r?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_179r" href="#177n" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_179r" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_179r')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_179r class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_179r" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_176j" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_176j" class="parent"><a name="176j" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_176j" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_176j" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_176j" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Patrick/">Patrick</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">23 October 2009 12:33:43AM</span><span class="votes " >15 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_176j'] = ['14 points', '15 points', '16 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_176j')">[+] (6 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_176j" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_176j" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Patrick/">Patrick</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">23 October 2009 12:33:43AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_176j'>15 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_176j'] = ['14 points', '15 points', '16 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_176j')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_176j" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>"Thus Aristotle laid it down that a heavy object falls faster than a light one does. The important thing about this idea is not that he was wrong, but that it never occurred to Aristotle to check it."
Albert Szent-Györgyi de Nagyrápolt, winner of the Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_176j"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_176j" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_176j')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_176j" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_176j')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_176j" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1co/rationality_quotes_october_2009/176j?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_176j" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_176j')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_176j class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_176j" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_176j" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_176j" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_17bz" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_17bz" class="parent"><a name="17bz" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_17bz" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_17bz" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_17bz" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/ArjenD/">ArjenD</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">24 October 2009 08:27:51AM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >6 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_17bz'] = ['5 points', '6 points', '7 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_17bz')">[+] (2 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_17bz" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_17bz" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/ArjenD/">ArjenD</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">24 October 2009 08:27:51AM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_17bz'>6 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_17bz'] = ['5 points', '6 points', '7 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_17bz')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_17bz" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>I checked Aristotle's 'On the Heavens' and 'Physics'. Nowhere could I find him saying that a heavy object falls faster than a light one. Aren't it the Aristotelian scholars who said that and who are to blame? Aristotle distinguished relative weight (our mass) and absolute weight (our mass density) and gives practical examples to check that denser objects move faster downwards in water than less dense objects, if the objects have the same shape.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_17bz"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_17bz" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_17bz')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_17bz" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_17bz')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_17bz" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1co/rationality_quotes_october_2009/17bz?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_17bz" href="#176j" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_17bz" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_17bz')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_17bz class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_17bz" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_17bz" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_17bz" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_17um" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_17um" class="parent"><a name="17um" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_17um" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_17um" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_17um" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/gwern/">gwern</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">31 October 2009 03:08:13AM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_17um'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_17um')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_17um" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_17um" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/gwern/">gwern</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">31 October 2009 03:08:13AM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_17um'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_17um'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_17um')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_17um" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>It's also worth noting that when you do Galileo's Tower of Pisa experiment, the heavier object <em>does</em> land first. (You think you release them at the same time, but you don't - your muscles let the heavier object go first.)</p>

<p>I find sometimes we here denigrate our distant predecessors too much; I have heard well-educated people call the Greeks fools for rejecting heliocentrism, despite the fact that the Greeks had powerful arguments against heliocentrism like the lack of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stellar_parallax#Early_theory_and_attempts" rel="nofollow">stellar parallax</a>, or we mock them for the 5 elements, despite the incredible feat of devising atomism just by considering basic logical paradoxes caused by alternative ontologies.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_17um"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_17um" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_17um')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_17um" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_17um')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_17um" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1co/rationality_quotes_october_2009/17um?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_17um" href="#17bz" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_17um" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_17um')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_17um class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_17um" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_17um" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_17um" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_17un" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_17un" class="parent"><a name="17un" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_17un" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_17un" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_17un" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/wedrifid/">wedrifid</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">31 October 2009 03:16:59AM</span><span class="votes " >0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_17un'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_17un')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_17un" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_17un" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/wedrifid/">wedrifid</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">31 October 2009 03:16:59AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_17un'>0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_17un'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_17un')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_17un" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>You think you release them at the same time, but you don't.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>And even if you do, there is air to consider.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_17un"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_17un" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_17un')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_17un" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_17un')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_17un" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1co/rationality_quotes_october_2009/17un?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_17un" href="#17um" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_17un" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_17un')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_17un class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_17un" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_176m" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_176m" class="parent"><a name="176m" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_176m" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_176m" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_176m" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/PhilGoetz/">PhilGoetz</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">23 October 2009 01:28:58AM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >10 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_176m'] = ['9 points', '10 points', '11 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_176m')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_176m" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_176m" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/PhilGoetz/">PhilGoetz</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">23 October 2009 01:28:58AM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_176m'>10 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_176m'] = ['9 points', '10 points', '11 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_176m')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_176m" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>A good point - but also note that, when Galileo argued against Artistotelian physics in his Dialogue Concerning the Two Chief World Systems, he set forth instead the idea of the inertial reference frame - but Galileo also never felt the need to perform an experiment to verify that his shipboard "experiments" would work as he predicted.  Both the wrong conclusion, and the right conclusion, were arrived at via thought-experiment.  And when Einstein took the next step by proposing the special theory of relativity, that too was a thought-experiment with no validation.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_176m"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_176m" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_176m')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_176m" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_176m')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_176m" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1co/rationality_quotes_october_2009/176m?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_176m" href="#176j" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_176m" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_176m')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_176m class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_176m" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_176m" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_176m" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_17bo" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_17bo" class="parent"><a name="17bo" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_17bo" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_17bo" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_17bo" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/komponisto/">komponisto</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">24 October 2009 06:11:25AM</span><span class="votes " >4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_17bo'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_17bo')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_17bo" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_17bo" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/komponisto/">komponisto</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">24 October 2009 06:11:25AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_17bo'>4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_17bo'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_17bo')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_17bo" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>In fact, one can go further, because Aristotle's conclusion was presumably arrived at in the first place through observation of everyday experience (indeed, it almost seems wrong to attribute it specifically to Aristotle since it is simply the "common sense" view of most of humanity, before and since). So here we arguably have an example of a thought experiment successfully refuting an empirically-derived hypothesis.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_17bo"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_17bo" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_17bo')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_17bo" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_17bo')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_17bo" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1co/rationality_quotes_october_2009/17bo?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_17bo" href="#176m" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_17bo" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_17bo')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_17bo class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_17bo" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_176k" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_176k" class="parent"><a name="176k" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_176k" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_176k" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_176k" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/RobinZ/">RobinZ</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">23 October 2009 12:41:29AM</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_176k'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_176k')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_176k" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_176k" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/RobinZ/">RobinZ</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">23 October 2009 12:41:29AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_176k'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_176k'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_176k')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_176k" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Just out of curiosity: do you know the origin of that quote? I've tried to find the citation before, but been unable.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_176k"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_176k" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_176k')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_176k" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_176k')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_176k" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1co/rationality_quotes_october_2009/176k?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_176k" href="#176j" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_176k" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_176k')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_176k class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_176k" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_176d" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_176d" class="parent"><a name="176d" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_176d" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_176d" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_176d" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/RichardKennaway/">RichardKennaway</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">22 October 2009 11:48:39PM</span><span class="votes " >17 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_176d'] = ['16 points', '17 points', '18 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_176d')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_176d" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_176d" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/RichardKennaway/">RichardKennaway</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">22 October 2009 11:48:39PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_176d'>17 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_176d'] = ['16 points', '17 points', '18 points' ];</script>