" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Technologos/">Technologos</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">31 October 2009 08:53:15PM</span><span class="votes " >0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_17vl'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_17vl')">[+] (15 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_17vl" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_17vl" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Technologos/">Technologos</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">31 October 2009 08:53:15PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_17vl'>0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_17vl'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_17vl')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_17vl" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Which is perhaps what you meant by "break the rules" (of construction), by using a marked ruler, for instance.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_17vl"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_17vl" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_17vl')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_17vl" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_17vl')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_17vl" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1co/rationality_quotes_october_2009/17vl?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_17vl" href="#17vk" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_17vl" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_17vl')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_17vl class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_17vl" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_17vl" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_17vl" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_17wg" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_17wg" class="parent"><a name="17wg" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_17wg" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_17wg" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_17wg" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/gwern/">gwern</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 November 2009 02:10:34PM</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_17wg'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_17wg')">[+] (14 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_17wg" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_17wg" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/gwern/">gwern</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 November 2009 02:10:34PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_17wg'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_17wg'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_17wg')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_17wg" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Right. There are some constructions like Archimedes's use of a marked ruler (which is covered, actually, in the 'Means to trisect angles by going outside the Greek framework' section) which work correctly &amp; are not immediately obviously breaking the rules. So I had to ask before I could know whether he had broken the rules or broken his proof (if you follow me).</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_17wg"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_17wg" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_17wg')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_17wg" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_17wg')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_17wg" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1co/rationality_quotes_october_2009/17wg?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_17wg" href="#17vl" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_17wg" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_17wg')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_17wg class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_17wg" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_17wg" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_17wg" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_17wi" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_17wi" class="parent"><a name="17wi" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_17wi" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_17wi" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_17wi" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Alicorn/">Alicorn</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 November 2009 02:40:01PM</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_17wi'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_17wi')">[+] (12 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_17wi" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_17wi" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Alicorn/">Alicorn</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 November 2009 02:40:01PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_17wi'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_17wi'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_17wi')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_17wi" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Couldn't you trisect a right angle by making an equilateral triangle with one of the right angle's lines for a side, then bisecting that angle of the triangle?  It wouldn't generalize to other angles, but you wouldn't need a ruler.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_17wi"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_17wi" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_17wi')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_17wi" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_17wi')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_17wi" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1co/rationality_quotes_october_2009/17wi?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_17wi" href="#17wg" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_17wi" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_17wi')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_17wi class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_17wi" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_17wi" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_17wi" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_17wk" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_17wk" class="parent"><a name="17wk" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_17wk" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_17wk" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_17wk" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/cousin_it/">cousin_it</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 November 2009 04:01:34PM</span><span class="votes " >3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_17wk'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_17wk')">[+] (11 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_17wk" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_17wk" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/cousin_it/">cousin_it</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 November 2009 04:01:34PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_17wk'>3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_17wk'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_17wk')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_17wk" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Of course you can trisect some angles, just not all of them. For example, you can't trisect the angle of an equilateral triangle (60 degrees).</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_17wk"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_17wk" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_17wk')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_17wk" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_17wk')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_17wk" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1co/rationality_quotes_october_2009/17wk?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_17wk" href="#17wi" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_17wk" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_17wk')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_17wk class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_17wk" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_17wk" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_17wk" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_17xp" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_17xp" class="parent"><a name="17xp" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_17xp" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_17xp" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_17xp" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/gwern/">gwern</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 November 2009 04:25:17AM</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_17xp'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_17xp')">[+] (10 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_17xp" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_17xp" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/gwern/">gwern</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 November 2009 04:25:17AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_17xp'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_17xp'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_17xp')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_17xp" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Just like you can solve the Halting Problem - for particular Turing Machines. The interesting impossibility results are always general.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_17xp"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_17xp" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_17xp')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_17xp" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_17xp')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_17xp" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1co/rationality_quotes_october_2009/17xp?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_17xp" href="#17wk" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_17xp" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_17xp')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_17xp class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_17xp" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_17xp" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_17xp" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_17yh" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_17yh" class="parent"><a name="17yh" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_17yh" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_17yh" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_17yh" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/cousin_it/">cousin_it</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 November 2009 10:05:49AM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_17yh'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_17yh')">[+] (9 childr