't1_178q')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_178q" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>What about the moment when you realize you've made a significant practical mistake?</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_178q"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_178q" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_178q')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_178q" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_178q')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_178q" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1co/rationality_quotes_october_2009/178q?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_178q" href="#173b" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_178q" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_178q')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_178q class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_178q" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_173m" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_173m" class="parent"><a name="173m" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_173m" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_173m" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_173m" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/loqi/">loqi</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">22 October 2009 05:25:32PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >11 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_173m'] = ['10 points', '11 points', '12 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_173m')">[+] (23 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_173m" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_173m" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/loqi/">loqi</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">22 October 2009 05:25:32PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_173m'>11 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_173m'] = ['10 points', '11 points', '12 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_173m')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_173m" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>That's a terrible quote. Being wrong is the <em>best possible outcome</em> of an argument, as it's the one with the highest expected knowledge gain (unless you're a hardcore altruist who doesn't value their own knowledge differently from anyone else's).</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_173m"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_173m" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_173m')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_173m" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_173m')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_173m" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1co/rationality_quotes_october_2009/173m?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_173m" href="#173b" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_173m" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_173m')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_173m class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_173m" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_173m" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_173m" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1760" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1760" class="parent"><a name="1760" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1760" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1760" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1760" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Emily/">Emily</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">22 October 2009 10:50:10PM</span><span class="votes " >6 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1760'] = ['5 points', '6 points', '7 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1760')">[+] (2 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1760" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1760" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Emily/">Emily</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">22 October 2009 10:50:10PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1760'>6 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1760'] = ['5 points', '6 points', '7 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1760')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1760" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>I agree with you, but I don't think that makes it a terrible quote. I personally don't seem to be psychologically able to avoid that awful sinking feeling when I realise I'm wrong, and it does suck. But recognising that it sucks is an important part of allowing the sinking feeling to wash over you, not be personally offended by it, and realise that if you update on this piece of wrongness, you're slightly less likely to be wrong again next time. For me at least, if I just try to pretend the sinking feeling isn't happening, because "rationally" it shouldn't, it just means I'm pretending the wrongness itself isn't happening. And that's a bad idea.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1760"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1760" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1760')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1760" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1760')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1760" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1co/rationality_quotes_october_2009/1760?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1760" href="#173m" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1760" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1760')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1760 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1760" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1760" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1760" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_17cl" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_17cl" class="parent"><a name="17cl" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_17cl" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_17cl" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_17cl" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/billswift/">billswift</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">24 October 2009 04:36:30PM</span><span class="votes " >2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_17cl'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_17cl')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_17cl" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_17cl" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/billswift/">billswift</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">24 October 2009 04:36:30PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_17cl'>2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_17cl'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_17cl')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_17cl" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Emotions help anchor new knowledge.  That horrible sinking feeling helps you to remember your screw up, so you don't do it again.  I suspect people that keep making the same mistakes are those who try to hide their mistakes from themselves and avoid that feeling.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_17cl"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_17cl" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_17cl')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_17cl" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_17cl')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_17cl" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1co/rationality_quotes_october_2009/17cl?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_17cl" href="#1760" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_17cl" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_17cl')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_17cl class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_17cl" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_176s" class="morechildren" ><div id="pre_t1_176s" class="parent"></div><div id="entry_t1_176s" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_176s" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'></div><div id="display_t1_176s" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"></div><div id="body_t1_176s" class="comment-content"><span class="morecomments"><a style="font-size: smaller; font-weight: bold" id="more_t1_176s" href="javascript:void()" onclick="return morechildren(this, 't3_1co', ['176s'], 3)">load more comments<span class="gray">&nbsp;(1 reply)</span></a></span></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_176s"></div><div class="comment-links"></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_176s" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_173v" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_173v" class="parent"><a name="173v" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_173v" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_173v" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_173v" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Douglas_Knight/">Douglas_Knight</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">22 October 2009 05:56:11PM</span><span class="votes " >6 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_173v'] = ['5 points', '6 points', '7 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_173v')">[+] (9 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_173v" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_173v" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Douglas_Knight/">Douglas_Knight</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">22 October 2009 05:56:11PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_173v'>6 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_173v'] = ['5 points', '6 points', '7 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_173v')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_173v" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>Being wrong is the best possible outcome of an argument, as it's the one with the highest expected knowledge gain</p>
</blockquote>

<p>No, that's backwards. Learning that you are wrong is good if and only if you are wrong. But it's only good because you were already wrong, which was bad - you were making bad decisions before. It's like saying that it is better to win the lottery than to be born rich. Roughly speaking, it doesn't matter when or where the money or knowledge comes from, only that you can use it.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_173v"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_173v" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_173v')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_173v" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_173v')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_173v" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1co/rationality_quotes_october_2009/173v?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_173v" href="#173m" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_173v" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_173v')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_173v class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_173v" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_173v" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_173v" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_174h" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_174h" class="parent"><a name="174h" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_174h" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_174h" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_174h" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/loqi/">loqi</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">22 October 2009 07:34:19PM</span><span class="votes " >6 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_174h'] = ['5 points', '6 points', '7 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_174h')">[+] (4 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_174h" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_174h" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/loqi/">loqi</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">22 October 2009 07:34:19PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_174h'>6 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_174h'] = ['5 points', '6 points', '7 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_174h')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_174h" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>So if you are surprised to find a $20 bill in your couch, your disappointment at having lost $20 some time in the past is equal to your pleasure at now having $20 more than you did a moment ago?</p>

<p>My current level of ignorance is a fact of life, I already know that there must be things that I'm wrong about. How is finding out something in particular that I <em>am</em> wrong about anything but a positive outcome?</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_174h"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_174h" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_174h')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_174h" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_174h')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_174h" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1co/rationality_quotes_october_2009/174h?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_174h" href="#173v" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_174h" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_174h')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_174h class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_174h" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_174h" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_174h" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_177a" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_177a" class="parent"><a name="177a" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_177a" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_177a" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_177a" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/wedrifid/">wedrifid</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">23 October 2009 04:25:36AM</span><span class="votes " >3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_177a'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_177a')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_177a" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_177a" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/wedrifid/">wedrifid</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">23 October 2009 04:25:36AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_177a'>3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_177a'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_177a')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_177a" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>So if you are surprised to find a $20 bill in your couch, your disappointment at having lost $20 some time in the past is equal to your pleasure at now having $20 more than you did a moment ago?</p>
</blockquote>

<p>That depends rather a lot on my dopamine levels and thought patterns. I gain much more pleasure from finding cash than I am disappointed at losing it. Hang on... Excuse me. Going for a walk around my house with my wallet open.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_177a"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_177a" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_177a')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_177a" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_177a')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_177a" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1co/rationality_quotes_october_2009/177a?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_177a" href="#174h" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_177a" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_177a')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_177a class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_177a" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_177a" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_177a" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_17bt" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_17bt" class="parent"><a name="17bt" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_17bt" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_17bt" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_17bt" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Technologos/">Technologos</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">24 October 2009 07:45:47AM</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_17bt'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_17bt')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_17bt" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_17bt" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Technologos/">Technologos</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">24 October 2009 07:45:47AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_17bt'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_17bt'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_17bt')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_17bt" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Careful... diminishing returns still apply ;)</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_17bt"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_17bt" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_17bt')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_17bt" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_17bt')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_17bt" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1co/rationality_quotes_october_2009/17bt?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_17bt" href="#177a" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_17bt" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_17bt')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_17bt class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_17bt" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1778" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1778" class="parent"><a name="1778" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1778" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1778" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1778" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Douglas_Knight/">Douglas_Knight</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">23 October 2009 03:53:49AM</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1778'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1778')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1778" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1778" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Douglas_Knight/">Douglas_Knight</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">23 October 2009 03:53:49AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1778'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1778'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1778')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1778" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>So if you are surprised to find a $20 bill in your couch, your disappointment at having lost $20 some time in the past is equal to your pleasure at now having $20 more than you did a moment ago?</p>
</blockquote>

<p>roughly, yes.</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>My current level of ignorance is a fact of life, I already know that there must be things that I'm wrong about. How is finding out something in particular that I am wrong about anything but a positive outcome?</p>
</blockquote>

<p>If your mistakes are independent, then correcting one of them doesn't (much) correct your estimate of how many more mistakes you have to correct. Say you have 21 beliefs with 95% confidence and an argument clarifies a random one of them. You still have 1 expected wrong belief. By independence, we might as well say it's belief #1 that gets clarified. People who were wrong about it end up the same as people who were right about it. Yes, they gained more information, but they were really just unlucky to start with less information. This is exactly the lottery/inheritance model.</p>

<p>Yes, your ignorance is a fact, but it's not a fact accessible to you. The argument decreases your estimate of your ignorance by the same amount, regardless of whether you win or lose. If you happen to know how ignorant you are, how many items you're wrong about, then the situation is different, but that's a lot less realistic than independence.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1778"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1778" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1778')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1778" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1778')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1778" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1co/rationality_quotes_october_2009/1778?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1778" href="#174h" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1778" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1778')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1778 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1778" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1778" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1778" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_177z" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_177z" class="parent"><a name="177z" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_177z" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_177z" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_177z" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/loqi/">loqi</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">23 October 2009 08:02:46AM</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_177z'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_177z')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_177z" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_177z" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/loqi/">loqi</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">23 October 2009 08:02:46AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_177z'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_177z'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_177z')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_177z" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>So if I understand the point you're making: Losing an argument provides enough evidence of your prior ignorance to prevent any net gain in <em>your expectation of your own overall knowledgeability</em>, at least relative to winning the argument.</p>

<p>I don't disagree, but I don't know why I'd care to base an emotional response on this kind of evaluation. I'm not fretting over my absolute position on the axis of knowledge, I'm just hill climbing. It's the first derivative that my decisions affect, not the initial constant.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_177z"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_177z" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_177z')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_177z" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_177z')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_177z" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1co/rationality_quotes_october_2009/177z?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_177z" href="#1778" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_177z" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_177z')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_177z class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_177z" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_174i" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_174i" class="parent"><a name="174i" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_174i" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_174i" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_174i" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/eirenicon/">eirenicon</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">22 October 2009 07:34:29PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_174i'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_174i')">[+] (3 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_174i" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_174i" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/eirenicon/">eirenicon</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">22 October 2009 07:34:29PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_174i'>2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_174i'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_174i')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_174i" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>It isn't that winning the lottery is better than being born rich, it's that winning the lottery is better than not winning the lottery. Even if you're already rich, winning the lottery is good. Presumably you weren't born right about everything, which means it's more useful to lose arguments than win them. After all, if you never lose an argument, what's more likely: that you <em>are</em> right about everything, that you're the best arguer ever, or that you simply don't argue things you're wrong about?</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_174i"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_174i" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_174i')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_174i" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_174i')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_174i" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1co/rationality_quotes_october_2009/174i?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_174i" href="#173v" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_174i" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_174i')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_174i class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_174i" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_174i" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_174i" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_176y" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_176y" class="parent"><a name="176y" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_176y" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_176y" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_176y" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/wedrifid/">wedrifid</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">23 October 2009 02:43:15AM</span><span class="votes " >0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_176y'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_176y')">[+] (2 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_176y" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_176y" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/wedrifid/">wedrifid</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">23 October 2009 02:43:15AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_176y'>0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_176y'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_176y')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_176y" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>After all, if you never lose an argument, what's more likely: that you are right about everything, that you're the best arguer ever, or that you simply don't argue things you're wrong about?</p>
</blockquote>

<p>My first thought was b). What was the intended response?</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_176y"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_176y" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_176y')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_176y" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_176y')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_176y" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1co/rationality_quotes_october_2009/176y?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_176y" href="#174i" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_176y" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_176y')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_176y class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_176y" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_176y" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_176y" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_17cn" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_17cn" class="parent"><a name="17cn" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_17cn" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_17cn" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_17cn" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/billswift/">billswift</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">24 October 2009 04:42:55PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_17cn'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_17cn')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_17cn" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_17cn" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/billswift/">billswift</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">24 October 2009 04:42:55PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_17cn'>2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_17cn'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_17cn')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_17cn" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Or that you are right about everything <strong>that you believe in strongly enough to argue about</strong>.</p>

<p>In other words, avoid believing strongly in the absence of evidence.  And don't argue where you don't have the facts on your side.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_17cn"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_17cn" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_17cn')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_17cn" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_17cn')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_17cn" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1co/rationality_quotes_october_2009/17cn?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_17cn" href="#176y" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_17cn" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_17cn')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_17cn class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_17cn" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1772" class="morechildren" ><div id="pre_t1_1772" class="parent"></div><div id="entry_t1_1772" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1772" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'></div><div id="display_t1_1772" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"></div><div id="body_t1_1772" class="comment-content"><span class="morecomments"><a style="font-size: smaller; font-weight: bold" id="more_t1_1772" href="javascript:void()" onclick="return morechildren(this, 't3_1co', ['1772'], 5)">load more comments<span class="gray">&nbsp;(1 reply)</span></a></span></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1772"></div><div class="comment-links"></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1772" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_173y" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_173y" class="parent"><a name="173y" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_173y" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_173y" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_173y" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Psychohistorian/">Psychohistorian</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">22 October 2009 06:14:25PM</span><span class="votes " >4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_173y'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_173y')">[+] (3 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_173y" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_173y" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Psychohistorian/">Psychohistorian</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">22 October 2009 06:14:25PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_173y'>4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_173y'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_173y')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_173y" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>It's more so a terrible quote because it is unwise to have a significant emotional attitude towards finding out you're wrong, because this will tend to reinforce irrational defense mechanisms ("Let's agree to disagree!"). The purpose of argument is, I hope, to improve your understanding of the world, so even if you shouldn't be thrilled to find yourself wrong, you shouldn't be afraid of doing so.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_173y"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_173y" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_173y')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_173y" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_173y')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_173y" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1co/rationality_quotes_october_2009/173y?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_173y" href="#173m" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_173y" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_173y')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_173y class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_173y" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_173y" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_173y" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1740" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1740" class="parent"><a name="1740" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1740" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1740" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1740" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Douglas_Knight/">Douglas_Knight</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">22 October 2009 06:24:15PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1740'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1740')">[+] (2 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1740" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1740" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Douglas_Knight/">Douglas_Knight</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">22 October 2009 06:24:15PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1740'>4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1740'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1740')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1740" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>It's more so a terrible quote because it is unwise to have a significant emotional attitude towards finding out you're wrong, because this will tend to reinforce irrational defense mechanisms</p>
</blockquote>

<p>Yes, it is unwise to have such emotional attitudes, but you don't get rid of them by saying that they are bad. Honestly acknowledging their existence, as in the original quote, is probably a better route to their elimination than an emotionless assertion that losing arguments is good. The quote, on its own, probably doesn't do much good, and perhaps does some harm, but I think it is probably a better step to accomplishing loqi's goal than his phrasing.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1740"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1740" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1740')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1740" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1740')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1740" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1co/rationality_quotes_october_2009/1740?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1740" href="#173y" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1740" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1740')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1740 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1740" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1740" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1740" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_174k" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_174k" class="parent"><a name="174k" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_174k" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_174k" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_174k" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/loqi/">loqi</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">22 October 2009 07:49:51PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_174k'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_174k')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_174k" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_174k" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/loqi/">loqi</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">22 October 2009 07:49:51PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_174k'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_174k'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_174k')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_174k" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>Honestly acknowledging their existence, as in the original quote, is probably a better route to their elimination than an emotionless assertion that losing arguments is good.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>Possibly, but I certainly wasn't advocating an emotionless response. Fight fire with fire! If you realize you're feeling stupid for having been wrong instead of feeling excited to have learned something, go ahead and feel stupid for feeling stupid.</p>

<p>I think I understand the rationale behind the original quote: Being wrong feels awful, so you should try to be right as often as possible. But this emotional response also disincentivizes attempts to <a href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/ig/i_defy_the_data/">stick your neck out</a> on behalf of your existing beliefs.</p>

<p>One might counter that a positive emotional response to being wrong provides an incentive for being wrong in the first place just so you can feel good about discarding your flawed beliefs in the future. This strikes me as a far less plausible mechanism than the above.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_174k"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_174k" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_174k')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_174k" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_174k')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_174k" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1co/rationality_quotes_october_2009/174k?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_174k" href="#1740" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_174k" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_174k')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_174k class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_174k" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_174k" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_174k" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1776" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1776" class="parent"><a name="1776" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1776" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1776" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1776" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Douglas_Knight/">Douglas_Knight</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">23 October 2009 03:24:10AM</span><span class="votes " >0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1776'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1776')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1776" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1776" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Douglas_Knight/">Douglas_Knight</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">23 October 2009 03:24:10AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1776'>0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1776'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1776')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1776" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>I think I understand the rationale behind the original quote: Being wrong feels awful, so you should try to be right as often as possible. But this emotional response also disincentivizes attempts to stick your neck out on behalf of your existing beliefs.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>I agree that this is a dangerous use of the original quote, which I admitted can be put to both good and bad uses.</p>

<p>I probably shouldn't have invoked you and definitely shouldn't have used "emotionless."</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1776"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1776" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1776')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1776" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1776')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1776" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1co/rationality_quotes_october_2009/1776?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1776" href="#174k" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1776" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1776')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1776 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1776" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_173t" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_173t" class="parent"><a name="173t" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_173t" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_173t" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_173t" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Jack/">Jack</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">22 October 2009 05:44:43PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_173t'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_173t')">[+] (5 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_173t" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_173t" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Jack/">Jack</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">22 October 2009 05:44:43PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_173t'>2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_173t'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_173t')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_173t" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Does anyone know the origin of this notion (that being wrong is the best outcome of an argument?). It strikes me as basically a founding principle of rationality and I'd like to know the earliest public reference to/ discussion of it. Alternately, is this sentiment summarized in any good quotes? It is hugely important for Hegel but he isn't, you know, pithy.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_173t"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_173t" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_173t')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_173t" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_173t')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_173t" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1co/rationality_quotes_october_2009/173t?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_173t" href="#173m" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_173t" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_173t')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_173t class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_173t" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_173t" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_173t" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_174l" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_174l" class="parent"><a name="174l" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_174l" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_174l" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_174l" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Benquo/">Benquo</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">22 October 2009 08:05:27PM</span><span class="votes " >9 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_174l'] = ['8 points', '9 points', '10 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_174l')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_174l" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_174l" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Benquo/">Benquo</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">22 October 2009 08:05:27PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_174l'>9 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_174l'] = ['8 points', '9 points', '10 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_174l')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_174l" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>This kind of sentiment pops up in Plato a lot, esp. in discussions of rhetoric, like here in Gorgias:</p>

<p>"For I count being refuted a greater good, insofar as it is a greater good to be rid of the greatest evil from oneself than to rid someone else of it.  I don't suppose that any evil for a man is as great as false belief about the things we're discussing right now."  (458a, Zeyl Translation)</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_174l"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_174l" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_174l')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_174l" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_174l')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_174l" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1co/rationality_quotes_october_2009/174l?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_174l" href="#173t" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_174l" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_174l')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_174l class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_174l" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_174l" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_174l" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_176g" class="morechildren" ><div id="pre_t1_176g" class="parent"></div><div id="entry_t1_176g" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_176g" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'></div><div id="display_t1_176g" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"></div><div id="body_t1_176g" class="comment-content"><span class="morecomments"><a style="font-size: smaller; font-weight: bold" id="more_t1_176g" href="javascript:void()" onclick="return morechildren(this, 't3_1co', ['176g'], 4)">load more comments<span class="gray">&nbsp;(1 reply)</span></a></span></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_176g"></div><div class="comment-links"></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_176g" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1742" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1742" class="parent"><a name="1742" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1742" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1742" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1742" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/SilasBarta/">SilasBarta</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">22 October 2009 06:32:44PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >6 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1742'] = ['5 points', '6 points', '7 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1742')">[+] (2 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1742" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1742" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/SilasBarta/">SilasBarta</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">22 October 2009 06:32:44PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1742'>6 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1742'] = ['5 points', '6 points', '7 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1742')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1742" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>In information theory, there's the concept of the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Surprisal" rel="nofollow">surprisal</a>, which is the logarithm of the inverse of the expected probability of an event.  The lower the probability, the higher the surprise(al).  The higher the surprisal, the greater the information content.</p>

<p>(Intuitively, the less likely something is, the more you change your beliefs upon learning it.)</p>

<p>So, yeah, it's pretty enshrined in information theory.  Entropy is equivalent to the (oxymoronic) "expected surprisal".  That is, given a discrete probability distribution over events, the probability-weighted average surprisal is the entropy.</p>

<p>Incidentally, as part of a project to convert all of the laws of physics into information-theoretic form, I realized that the elastic energy of a deformable body tells you its probability of being in that state, and (by the above argument), it's information content.  That means you can explain failure modes in terms of the component being forced to store more information than it's capable of.</p>

<p>Well, it's interesting to <em>me</em>.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1742"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1742" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1742')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1742" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1742')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1742" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1co/rationality_quotes_october_2009/1742?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1742" href="#173t" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1742" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1742')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1742 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1742" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1742" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1742" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1743" class="morechildren" ><div id="pre_t1_1743" class="parent"></div><div id="entry_t1_1743" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1743" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'></div><div id="display_t1_1743" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"></div><div id="body_t1_1743" class="comment-content"><span class="morecomments"><a style="font-size: smaller; font-weight: bold" id="more_t1_1743" href="javascript:void()" onclick="return morechildren(this, 't3_1co', ['1743'], 4)">load more comments<span class="gray">&nbsp;(2 replies)</span></a></span></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1743"></div><div class="comment-links"></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1743" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_174n" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_174n" class="parent"><a name="174n" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_174n" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_174n" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_174n" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Eliezer_Yudkowsky/">Eliezer_Yudkowsky</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">22 October 2009 08:13:33PM</span><span class="votes " >2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_174n'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_174n')">[+] (15 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_174n" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_174n" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Eliezer_Yudkowsky/">Eliezer_Yudkowsky</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">22 October 2009 08:13:33PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_174n'>2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_174n'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_174n')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_174n" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Why is this being voted down?  I'm pretty sure Nominull didn't post the quote in order to endorse it as a normative sentiment.  There's an ick reaction so you hit "Vote down"?  But that's not what decides whether a quote is a good thing to have read!</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_174n"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_174n" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_174n')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_174n" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_174n')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_174n" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1co/rationality_quotes_october_2009/174n?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_174n" href="#173b" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_174n" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_174n')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_174n class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_174n" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_174n" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_174n" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_174r" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_174r" class="parent"><a name="174r" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_174r" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_174r" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_174r" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/eirenicon/">eirenicon</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">22 October 2009 08:19:31PM</span><span class="votes " >3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_174r'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_174r')">[+] (11 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_174r" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_174r" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/eirenicon/">eirenicon</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">22 October 2009 08:19:31PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_174r'>3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_174r'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_174r')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_174r" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Also, in general, the quote is accurate. While it is intellectually useful to be proven wrong, it is not really a pleasant feeling, because it's much nicer to have already been right. This is especially true if you are heavily invested in what you are wrong about, eg. a scientist who realizes his research was based on an erroneous premise will be happy to stop wasting time but will also feel pretty crappy about the time he's already wasted. It's not in our nature to be purely cerebral about such a devastating thing as <em>being wrong</em> can be.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_174r"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_174r" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_174r')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_174r" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_174r')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_174r" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1co/rationality_quotes_october_2009/174r?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_174r" href="#174n" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_174r" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_174r')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_174r class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_174r" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_174r" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_174r" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_174v" class="morechildren" ><div id="pre_t1_174v" class="parent"></div><div id="entry_t1_174v" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_174v" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'></div><div id="display_t1_174v" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"></div><div id="body_t1_174v" class="comment-content"><span class="morecomments"><a style="font-size: smaller; font-weight: bold" id="more_t1_174v" href="javascript:void()" onclick="return morechildren(this, 't3_1co', ['174v'], 3)">load more comments<span class="gray">&nbsp;(11 replies)</span></a></span></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_174v"></div><div class="comment-links"></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_174v" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_175b" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_175b" class="parent"><a name="175b" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_175b" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_175b" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_175b" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/SilasBarta/">SilasBarta</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">22 October 2009 09:07:41PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_175b'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_175b')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_175b" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_175b" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/SilasBarta/">SilasBarta</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">22 October 2009 09:07:41PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_175b'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_175b'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_175b')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_175b" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>I think the only ick reaction here is from my <a href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1co/rationality_quotes_october_2009/173j">examples</a> of experiences that are much more painful than any epistemic event.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_175b"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_175b" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_175b')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_175b" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_175b')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_175b" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1co/rationality_quotes_october_2009/175b?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_175b" href="#174n" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_175b" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_175b')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_175b class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_175b" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_175b" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_175b" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_176v" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_176v" class="parent"><a name="176v" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_176v" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_176v" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_176v" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/wedrifid/">wedrifid</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">23 October 2009 02:30:54AM</span><span class="votes " >3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_176v'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_176v')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_176v" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_176v" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/wedrifid/">wedrifid</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">23 October 2009 02:30:54AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_176v'>3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_176v'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_176v')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_176v" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>(Agree, and add that) It is often more frustrating when I realise I am <em>not</em> wrong, can reliably reverse engineer the other's thought process, know that they will jump back to this error whenever an even tangentially related topic is discussed and I must now choose between rapport and reason. The death cry of mutual respect.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_176v"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_176v" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_176v')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_176v" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_176v')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_176v" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1co/rationality_quotes_october_2009/176v?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_176v" href="#175b" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_176v" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_176v')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_176v class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_176v" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_174q" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_174q" class="parent"><a name="174q" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_174q" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_174q" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_174q" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/RobinZ/">RobinZ</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">22 October 2009 08:18:17PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_174q'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_174q')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_174q" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_174q" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/RobinZ/">RobinZ</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">22 October 2009 08:18:17PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_174q'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_174q'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_174q')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_174q" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>I didn't downvote, but I didn't upvote either. The trouble is that a moment's thought reveals a host of objections. If I understand correctly, rationality quotes ought to be good, useful cached thoughts; this is merely a useful observation.</p>

<p>(Edit: On further reflection, I've upvoted it. Points to eirenicon.)</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_174q"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_174q" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_174q')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_174q" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_174q')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_174q" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1co/rationality_quotes_october_2009/174q?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_174q" href="#174n" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_174q" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_174q')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_174q class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_174q" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_173j" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_173j" class="parent"><a name="173j" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_173j" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_173j" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_173j" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/SilasBarta/">SilasBarta</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">22 October 2009 05:12:33PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_173j'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_173j')">[+] (2 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_173j" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_173j" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/SilasBarta/">SilasBarta</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">22 October 2009 05:12:33PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_173j'>3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_173j'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_173j')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_173j" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Hm, what about being constipated with hemorrhoids?</p>

<p><strong>ETA:</strong> No wait, how about this: same as above, but, assuming you're a male, with the intestines so full that they press against the prostate (basically the "core" of your pleasure/pain generator) and keep you from being able to urinate.</p>

<p>Then, top it off with a severe hangover headache.</p>

<p>Who would prefer being proven wrong to all of that?  Me.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_173j"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_173j" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_173j')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_173j" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_173j')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_173j" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/1co/rationality_quotes_october_2009/173j?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_173j" href="#173b" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_173j" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_173j')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_173j class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_173j" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_173j" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_173j" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_173r" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_173r" class="parent"><a name="173r" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_173r" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_173r" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_173r" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Cyan/">Cyan</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">22 October 2009 05:37:02PM</span><span class="votes " >2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_173r'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_173r')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_173r" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_173r" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Cyan/">Cyan</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">22 October 2009 05:37:02PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_173r'>2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_173r'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_173r')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_173r" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Yup, that's way worse.</p>

